This document describes the compilation and installation procedures
for Beluga.


*      [Pre-requisites](#01)

*      [Building](#02)

*      [Installing](#03)


Pre-requisites
==============

* [ocaml 3.10][01] or greater
* [camlp5][02]
* [extlib][03]
* [ledit][04]
* [ulex][05]

[01]: http://localhost
[02]: http://localhost
[03]: http://localhost
[04]: http://localhost
[05]: http://localhost


Building
========

The Simple Way
--------------

If you just want to build everything and immediately install it, do
the following:

    $ cd src
    $ make
    $ make install

This will install the Beluga intepreter into `/usr/local/bin`.  If you
wish to change the install location, simply edit the appropriate
variables in `Makefile`.


Compiling Everything
--------------------

If you wish to compile everything at once:

    $ cd src
    $ make


Compiling the Beluga Library
----------------------------

If you wish to compile just the Beluga library:

    $ cd src
    $ cd make belugalib


Building the Documentation
--------------------------

    $ cd src
    $ make doc


Compiling the Beluga-specific Toplevel
--------------------------------------

If you wish to compile the Beluga toplevel:

    $ cd src
    $ make top


Interacting with the Beluga-specific Toplevel
---------------------------------------------

If you wish to easily interact with the Beluga toplevel:

    $ cd src
    $ make interactive

The `interactive` target will compile the beluga library and toplevel
and then immediately load the toplevel with the appropriate flags.

This target is intended to be used during the development cycle.
After you make changes to the code, simply run `make interactive` to
recompile the code and drop into the toplevel to experiment with the
changes you just made.



Installing
==========

To install the Beluga interpreter after you have compiled everything,
simply issue:

    $ cd src
    $ make install
